                    <descriptiveNote><p>Qánqon-Kámek-Klaúla was a well known healer and prophet and his history was shared and kept among the Kutenai, his people. He was also referenced in David Thompson's journals while young and living as a woman and then later by Thompson again and his contemporaries as a 'Manlike Woman' who carried men's weapons and had a wife.</p></descriptiveNote>
                </localDescription>
                <localDescription localType="gender">
